{
  "texts": [
    "At low temperatures, the model tends to produce more deterministic outputs, while at higher temperatures, the outputs become more varied, creative, and potentially less coherent (Nakaishi and Hukushima, 2022; Suri et al., 2024).",
    "The temperature for all of the LLM's API through all the functions was adjusted to 0 to ensure consistent and fixed output, except that the temperature for Stage 6, idea generation, was set to 1 to enhance the LLM's creativity during the process of generating ideas.",
    "We input a design problem as a sentence.",
    "It is common for a design problem to be vague and unclear, especially in the initial design stages (Zeng and Gu, 1999a).",
    "Therefore, it is important to gather information to clarify the design problem for designers."
  ]
}